nhc_headline: ...GABRIELLE MOVING QUICKLY EAST-NORTHEASTWARD AND EXPECTED TO BE NEAR OR OVER THE AZORES AS A HURRICANE BY LATE THURSDAY OR EARLY FRIDAY...
summary: ...GABRIELLE MOVING QUICKLY EAST-NORTHEASTWARD AND EXPECTED TO BE NEAR OR OVER THE AZORES AS A HURRICANE BY LATE THURSDAY OR EARLY FRIDAY... As of 2:00 AM AST Wed Sep 24 the center of Gabrielle was located near 35.3, -52.7 with movement ENE at 22 mph. The minimum central pressure was 954 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 120 mph.
